longBusinessSummary: Granite Creek Copper Ltd., an exploration company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties. Its principal property is the Stu copper-gold-silver project that consists of 541 contiguous claims covering approximately 11,100 hectares in Yukon Territory, Canada. The company was formerly known as Granite Creek Gold Ltd. and changed its name to Granite Creek Copper Ltd. in October 2018. Granite Creek Copper Ltd. was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
